    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 02, 2026</p>
    <p>Welcome to <strong>ArcLine</strong>. Your privacy is critically important to us. This policy explains how we handle information in our mobile application.</p>

    <h2>1. Information Collection and Use</h2>
    <p>ArcLine is designed as an offline 3D creative tool. We do <strong>not</strong> collect, store, or transmit any personally identifiable information (PII) such as your name, email address, physical address, or phone number.</p>

    <h2>2. Local Data Storage</h2>
    <p>All game progress, settings, and 3D creations are stored <strong>locally on your device</strong>. This data never leaves your device and is not accessible by the developer or any third party. If you uninstall the app, this local data may be deleted by the Android system.</p>

    <h2>3. Permissions</h2>
    <p>The App may request basic technical permissions required for its operation (such as Internet access for internal engine loading). However, no private user data, media files, or contacts are accessed or shared.</p>

    <h2>4. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>Our application is safe for users of all ages. Because we do not collect any personal data, we do not knowingly collect or solicit information from children under the age of 13.</p>

    <h2>5. Security</h2>
    <p>Since the app functions offline and does not transmit data over the internet, your creations and data remain secure within your own device.</p>

    <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.</p>

